"{\"uid\": \"jamaicaobserver.com-2024-08-12-usa-fend-off-france-womens-olympic-basketball-gold\", \"entities\": [{\"sentence\": \"PARIS, France (AFP) - The United States held off France 67-66 to win an unprecedented eighth-successive women's Olympic basketball gold on Sunday and extend their run of victories at the tournament to 61 games.\", \"from\": 0, \"to\": 210, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 7, \"end\": 13, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9497727278290977, \"rank\": 0.052839586051214846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 26, \"end\": 39, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999089423041, \"rank\": 5.311734637705821e-08, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 49, \"end\": 55, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9497727278290977, \"rank\": 0.052839586051214846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A'ja Wilson scored a game-high 21 points for the Americans who won the title for the 10th time overall, surviving a buzzer-beating shot from France's Gabby Williams.\", \"from\": 212, \"to\": 377, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 212, \"end\": 223, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"A'ja Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\"}, {\"begin\": 353, \"end\": 359, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9497727278290977, \"rank\": 0.052839586051214846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 362, \"end\": 376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Williams\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Gabby Williams\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Williams\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gabby_Williams\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The hosts needed a three to force overtime in Paris but Williams' foot was on the three-point line as she let go of the ball, so her shot counted for just two points in a dramatic finale.\", \"from\": 379, \"to\": 566, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 425, \"end\": 430, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 9.155514403885618e-15, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"It's all a blur right now,\\\" said Wilson, who also registered 13 rebounds and four blocks.\", \"from\": 568, \"to\": 658, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 602, \"end\": 608, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9282459879815225e-28, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"We were just resilient and when we needed to we just kept going.\\\"\", \"from\": 660, \"to\": 726, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Kelsey Plum and Kahleah Copper both scored 12 points off the bench for the US.\", \"from\": 728, \"to\": 806, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 728, \"end\": 739, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelsey_Plum\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Kelsey Plum\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelsey_Plum\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kelsey_Plum\"}, {\"begin\": 803, \"end\": 805, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4688665466752805e-11, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Williams led France with 19.\", \"from\": 807, \"to\": 835, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 820, \"end\": 826, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9497727278290977, \"rank\": 0.052839586051214846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"An eighth-straight triumph gave the US women the record for most consecutive gold medals in any team sport at the Olympics, breaking a tie with the US men, who won seven basketball titles in a row from 1936 to 1968.\", \"from\": 837, \"to\": 1052, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 873, \"end\": 875, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4688665466752805e-11, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 985, \"end\": 987, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4688665466752805e-11, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"That was an absolutely incredible basketball game.\", \"from\": 1054, \"to\": 1105, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Two teams that left it all out there,\\\" said US Coach Cheryl Reeve.\", \"from\": 1106, \"to\": 1172, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1159, \"end\": 1171, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cheryl_Reeve\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cheryl Reeve\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cheryl_Reeve\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cheryl_Reeve\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Coming home with gold, I can not think of anything greater in life than what we just did together.\\\"\", \"from\": 1174, \"to\": 1274, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"For the 42-year-old Diana Taurasi it was a record sixth Olympic gold, moving her one ahead of Sue Bird.\", \"from\": 1276, \"to\": 1379, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1296, \"end\": 1309, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Diana Taurasi\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Diana_Taurasi\"}, {\"begin\": 1370, \"end\": 1378, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Bird\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Sue Bird\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Bird\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sue_Bird\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US women got support from LeBron James, who sat courtside wearing his gold medal and was joined by team-mates Bam Adebayo and Derrick White, after they won the men's gold by beating France 98-87 in Saturday's final.\", \"from\": 1381, \"to\": 1600, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1385, \"end\": 1387, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4688665466752805e-11, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1411, \"end\": 1423, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"LeBron James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/LeBron_James\"}, {\"begin\": 1499, \"end\": 1506, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bam_Adebayo\", \"score\": 0.9999999999931788, \"rank\": 6.717569134881624e-12, \"text\": \"Adebayo\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bam_Adebayo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Bam_Adebayo\"}, {\"begin\": 1511, \"end\": 1524, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derrick_White_(basketball)\", \"score\": 0.9925925345590776, \"rank\": 0.006633499170812927, \"text\": \"Derrick White\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derrick_White_(basketball)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Derrick_White_(basketball)\"}, {\"begin\": 1567, \"end\": 1576, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1998_FIFA_World_Cup\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 4.569200727929223e-30, \"text\": \"France 98\", \"types\": [\"Q500834\", \"Q1656682\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1998_FIFA_World_Cup\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/1998_FIFA_World_Cup\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was the first time in Games history the men's and women's finals featured identical match-ups.\", \"from\": 1602, \"to\": 1699, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"A low-scoring first quarter saw a cold-shooting France muster just nine points, but the US only fared marginally better and led by six after 10 minutes.\", \"from\": 1701, \"to\": 1853, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1749, \"end\": 1755, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9497727278290977, \"rank\": 0.052839586051214846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 1789, \"end\": 1791, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4688665466752805e-11, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Nevada-born Williams, who qualifies to play for France through her mother, trimmed the gap to a point with a three early in the second period before a basket from Valeriane Ayayi tied the game at 20-20.\", \"from\": 1855, \"to\": 2057, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1903, \"end\": 1909, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9497727278290977, \"rank\": 0.052839586051214846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Marine Fauthoux drained a three from near midcourt with the shot clock expiring to send the Bercy Arena crowd wild, but Napheesa Collier's putback ensured the teams headed into the break level at 25-25.\", \"from\": 2059, \"to\": 2261, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2059, \"end\": 2074, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Fauthoux\", \"score\": 0.99989788370849, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marine Fauthoux\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Fauthoux\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Fauthoux\"}, {\"begin\": 2151, \"end\": 2162, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Bercy Arena\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Accor_Arena\"}, {\"begin\": 2179, \"end\": 2195, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napheesa_Collier\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Napheesa Collier\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napheesa_Collier\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Napheesa_Collier\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"France strung together a 10-point run to start the third period as Fauthoux and Ayayi both nailed threes.\", \"from\": 2263, \"to\": 2368, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2263, \"end\": 2269, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9497727278290977, \"rank\": 0.052839586051214846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US hit back to lead 45-43 going into the final quarter, with Plum connecting on a pair of threes, one after Marine Johannes took a nasty blow from Wilson that went unpunished, to France's fury.\", \"from\": 2370, \"to\": 2567, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2374, \"end\": 2376, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4688665466752805e-11, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2482, \"end\": 2497, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Johann\\u00e8s\", \"score\": 0.9999879852360758, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Marine Johannes\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Johann\\u00e8s\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Marine_Johann\\u00e8s\"}, {\"begin\": 2521, \"end\": 2527, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9282459879815225e-28, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\"}, {\"begin\": 2553, \"end\": 2559, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9497727278290977, \"rank\": 0.052839586051214846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wilson belatedly found some rhythm offensively after a difficult first half, but France had an answer each time and went back in front, 51-49, on Marieme Badiane's layup.\", \"from\": 2569, \"to\": 2739, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2569, \"end\": 2575, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9282459879815225e-28, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\"}, {\"begin\": 2650, \"end\": 2656, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9497727278290977, \"rank\": 0.052839586051214846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The US nudged back ahead, Wilson getting a kind bounce off the backboard and Plum sinking a pair of free throws to leave them leading by three with two minutes to play.\", \"from\": 2741, \"to\": 2909, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2745, \"end\": 2747, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4688665466752805e-11, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2767, \"end\": 2773, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9282459879815225e-28, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Williams' jumper made it a one-point contest before Copper drove to the basket to keep the US on top.\", \"from\": 2911, \"to\": 3012, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3002, \"end\": 3004, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4688665466752805e-11, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A travelling call against Wilson gave the ball back to France with around 45 seconds left, but Fauthoux's desperation three came up well short under pressure from Breanna Stewart.\", \"from\": 3014, \"to\": 3193, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3040, \"end\": 3046, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9282459879815225e-28, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\"}, {\"begin\": 3069, \"end\": 3075, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9497727278290977, \"rank\": 0.052839586051214846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3177, \"end\": 3192, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breanna_Stewart\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Breanna Stewart\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breanna_Stewart\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Breanna_Stewart\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Wilson then made a free throw to extend the lead to four and Plum looked to have clinched the win with a pair of foul shots, but Williams kept France alive with a clutch three.\", \"from\": 3195, \"to\": 3371, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3195, \"end\": 3201, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.9282459879815225e-28, \"text\": \"Wilson\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q3665646\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/A'ja_Wilson\"}, {\"begin\": 3338, \"end\": 3344, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9497727278290977, \"rank\": 0.052839586051214846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Copper held her nerve to sink two more free throws for the US to restore their cushion to three.\", \"from\": 3373, \"to\": 3469, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3432, \"end\": 3434, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999999854481, \"rank\": 1.4688665466752805e-11, \"text\": \"US\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"They needed every point as Williams nearly pulled off a miraculous escape act as the buzzer sounded, only to be denied by a matter of centimetres.\", \"from\": 3471, \"to\": 3617, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The United States women's basketball team poses for a photo after the gold medal game at AccorHotels Arena in Lille, France, on Sunday.\", \"from\": 3619, \"to\": 3754, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3623, \"end\": 3636, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"score\": 0.9999999089423041, \"rank\": 5.311734637705821e-08, \"text\": \"United States\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_men's_national_basketball_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3729, \"end\": 3734, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille_OSC\", \"score\": 0.9999952996837653, \"rank\": 4.70033839701805e-06, \"text\": \"Lille\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille_OSC\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Lille_OSC\"}, {\"begin\": 3736, \"end\": 3742, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9497727278290977, \"rank\": 0.052839586051214846, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"HOUSE RULES\", \"from\": 3758, \"to\": 3769, \"entities\": []}]}"